## 🍎 macOS Installation Guide

> IMPORTANT: The .exe file is Windows-only. macOS users must run the Python script directly.


### Step 1: Install Python 3

Open Terminal (Cmd + Space, type "Terminal") and run:

    python3 --version

If Python is not installed, install via Homebrew:

    /bin/bash -c "$(curl -fsSL https://raw.githubusercontent.com/Homebrew/install/HEAD/install.sh)"
    brew install python3


### Step 2: Install Required Dependencies

In Terminal, run:

    pip3 install deep-translator PyQt5


### Step 3: Download and Run LocalizeIt

    git clone https://github.com/yourusername/LocalizeIt.git
    cd LocalizeIt
    python3 main.py


### Optional: Create a macOS App Bundle

To create a double-clickable .app file:

    pip3 install pyinstaller
    pyinstaller --noconsole --onefile --windowed --name LocalizeIt main.py
    open dist/

Now double-click LocalizeIt.app to run!


### Troubleshooting macOS Issues

"pip3: command not found"
    python3 -m ensurepip --upgrade

"No module named 'PyQt5'"
    pip3 install --user PyQt5

"Permission denied"
    chmod +x main.py

App crashes? Run from Terminal to see error:
    cd /path/to/LocalizeIt
    python3 main.py


### Requirements Summary (macOS)

Python           3.7+           brew install python3
deep-translator  Latest         pip3 install deep-translator
PyQt5            Latest         pip3 install PyQt5
PyInstaller      Latest         pip3 install pyinstaller (optional)


Note: The application works identically on macOS and Windows.
Only the packaging method differs.